This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an extension to the ExpertMatcher framework for automating ML model selection. It also involves the use of autoencoders, which are commonly used in ML research. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields often involve the use of ML models. The paper may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with the matching of model components. Finally, it could also be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves the processing of natural language data.
